parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock mechanism can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues if the door cannot be opened in an emergency situation.
symptoms: The door lock mechanism fails to unlock on the first pull
requiring multiple presses of the door lock/unlock button to open the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Twisted Bowden Cable Causing Door Locking Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The twisted Bowden cable can cause the driver-side door to remain locked, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle in emergency situations, such as a fire or dead battery, which can lead to serious safety risks.
symptoms: The driver-side door cannot be opened from the inside when the door is locked
the door can only be opened using the center unlock button
difficulty opening the door in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC blower/fan motor can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The HVAC blower/fan motor stops working after a certain period of driving (approximately 45 minutes)
the blower/fan motor works initially but stops functioning after a while.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door lock system can cause the doors to remain locked, trapping occupants inside the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The doors will not unlock from the inside when pulling the handle
the "double-pull" operation to unlock the door malfunctions intermittently
the doors remain locked even when the vehicle is stationary and the engine is not operating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning indicator illuminates
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
side airbags deploy but front airbags do not.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt and Airbag System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt and airbag system can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning indicator illuminates
seat belt and airbag system failure diagnosis
failure to deploy airbags in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on busy roads or highways. This can lead to a loss of control, collision, or injury.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to restart
the vehicle stalls without warning
the engine hydro locks due to water entering the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Driver Side Mirror Malfunction)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the driver side mirror can cause the driver to lose visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when merging or changing lanes. This can lead to a loss of control, collision, or injury.
symptoms: The driver side mirror is not working
the mirror does not respond to controls
the mirror is unable to adjust
the driver has reduced visibility while driving.
